      "body": "Nice catch! Concept ACK\r\n\r\nI believe `CheckMinimalPush` is mostly tested in `script_json_test` (testcases in `src/test/data/script_tests.json`), however, it wouldn't be practical to include the 65535 bytes string there, so it makes sense to have a separate test for that.\r\n\r\nWhile we're at it, should we also check that 65536 bytes uses OP_PUSHDATA4?\r\nEDIT: this is incorrect: https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/34919#issuecomment-4130698804\r\n\r\n```diff\r\ndiff --git a/src/test/script_tests.cpp b/src/test/script_tests.cpp\r\nindex b07870207c..87dc079a12 100644\r\n--- a/src/test/script_tests.cpp\r\n+++ b/src/test/script_tests.cpp\r\n@@ -1461,6 +1461,11 @@ BOOST_AUTO_TEST_CASE(script_CheckMinimalPush_boundary)\r\n     std::vector<unsigned char> data(65535, '\\x42');\r\n     BOOST_CHECK(CheckMinimalPush(data, OP_PUSHDATA2));\r\n     BOOST_CHECK(!CheckMinimalPush(data, OP_PUSHDATA4));\r\n+\r\n+    // Test the boundary at exactly 65536 bytes: must use OP_PUSHDATA4.\r\n+    std::vector<unsigned char> data2(65536, '\\x42');\r\n+    BOOST_CHECK(!CheckMinimalPush(data2, OP_PUSHDATA2));\r\n+    BOOST_CHECK(CheckMinimalPush(data2, OP_PUSHDATA4));\r\n }\r\n \r\n BOOST_AUTO_TEST_CASE(script_GetScriptAsm)\t\r\n```",
      "user": {
